<p>
<h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
<p>
    2.1. User Notes: We use your diary notes solely to provide you with diary functionality and to ensure that your
    notes are safely and securely stored. We do not use your notes for any other purposes.
</p>
<p>
    2.2. Anonymous Data: We use anonymous data to improve our application and to gain insights into how users interact
    with our application. We also use this data to diagnose technical issues and to ensure that our application is
    running optimally.
</p>
<h3>3. How We Share Your Information</h3>
<p>
    3.1. User Notes: We do not share your diary notes with any third-party. We may, however, share your notes with
    OpenAI to help improve the artificial intelligence technology that powers our application. If we do share your notes
    with OpenAI, we will anonymize them first to protect your privacy.
</p>

<p>
    3.2. Anonymous Data: We share anonymous data with Plausible analytics service to help us understand how our
    application is used and to improve its performance. We do not share any personally identifiable information with
    Plausible analytics service.
</p>

<h3>4. Your Rights and Choices</h3>
<p>
    4.1. Access and Correction: You can access and correct your diary notes at any time by logging into our application
    and editing your notes.
</p>
<p>
    4.2. Deletion: You can delete your diary notes at any time by logging into our application and deleting your notes.
    Once deleted, your notes cannot be recovered.

</p>
<p>
    4.3. Opt-Out: You can opt-out of sharing anonymous data with Plausible analytics service by disabling the
    "Analytics" option in our application settings.
</p>

